A: The NullPointerException is likely because you are trying to call findViewById() before setContentView() has been called. The setContentView() method must be called before findViewById() because it sets the layout for the activity.
In your MainActivity, you should call setContentView(R.layout.activity_main) before calling helper.setupDatePicker().
Here's how your onCreate() method should look:
protected void onCreate(Bundle savedInstanceState) {
    super.onCreate(savedInstanceState);
    requestWindowFeature(Window.FEATURE_NO_TITLE);
    getWindow().setFlags(WindowManager.LayoutParams.FLAG_FULLSCREEN, WindowManager.LayoutParams.FLAG_FULLSCREEN);
    setContentView(R.layout.activity_main); // Set the layout for the activity
    AlarmHelper helper = new AlarmHelper();
    helper.setupDatePicker();
}

Also, you should consider extending ListActivity instead of Activity if you're going to use a ListView. This will give you a ListView that you can easily access with getListView().

